In a large bowl, beat eggs, add sugar and canola oil. Measure flour, baking powder, baking soda and spices. Sift together and add to the first mixture. Fold in carrots, pecans, pineapple and coconut. Pour into a 9 x 13 lightly oiled pan and bake at 350 degrees F for 45 - 60 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cream softened cream cheese and butter. Add icing sugar, and just enough orange juice to make fairly stiff icing. Ice cake and sprinkle with orange peel. Chill to set icing.